<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="317">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181800" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole lourothi Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lourothi">Pheidole lourothi</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="317">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="317">Etymology Named in honor of Louis M. Roth, distinguished insect systematist and friend, who accompanied me on my first field trip to Costa Rica in 1959.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="317">
Diagnosis A very large blackish (major) or reddish (minor) brown member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group, distinguished in the major by its long propodeal spines, largely rugoreticulate dorsal head surface, and almost completely rugulose and carinulate sides of the mesosoma; and in the minor by the rugulose mesopleuron and propodeum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="317">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33573" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole ajax Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole ajax Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ajax">ajax</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33743" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fiorii Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fiorii Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fiorii">fiorii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole hector Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole hector Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hector">hector</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33782" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole hirsuta Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole hirsuta Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">hirsuta</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181792" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jaculifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jaculifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaculifera">jaculifera</taxonomicName>
, differing in many details of body form, sculpturing, and pilosity, as illustrated. Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.88, HL 1.80, SL 1.04, EL 0.30, PW 0.84. Paratype minor: HW 0.78, HL 0.92, SL 1.16, EL 0.22, PW 0.60.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="317">color Major: body blackish brown, head also with a faint reddish tinge; mandibles dark reddish brown; scape and legs except tarsi medium brown; funiculus and tarsi brownish yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="317">Minor: gaster dark brown, rest of body medium reddish brown; appendages light reddish brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="317">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="317">Biology The type colony was collected by Philip S. Ward from a rotten log on the floor of rainforest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="317">Figure Upper: holotype, major. Lower: paratype, minor. COSTA RICA: 4 km south-southeast of San Vito Puntarenas (Philip S. Ward). Scale bars = 1 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
